Day 3 Task: Basic Linux Commands

Task: What is the linux command to

To view what's written in a file.
 - cat filename
To change the access permissions of files.
 - chmod 
To check which commands you have run till now.
 - History
To remove a directory/ Folder.
 -  rm directoryname
To create a fruits.txt file and to view the content.
 -  touch fruits.txt
 -  cat fruits.txt
Add content in devops.txt (One in each line) - Apple, Mango, Banana, Cherry, Kiwi, Orange, Guava.
 -  sudo vi devops.txt
To Show only top three fruits from the file.
 - head -n 3 fruits.txt
To Show only bottom three fruits from the file.
 - tail -n 3 fruits.txt
To create another file Colors.txt and to view the content.
 - touch colors.txt
 -cat colors.txt
Add content in Colors.txt (One in each line) - Red, Pink, White, Black, Blue, Orange, Purple, Grey.
 - sudo vi  colors.txt
To find the difference between fruits.txt and Colors.txt file.
 - diff fruits.txt colors.txt


Something More:)

Login methods in Linux :-
1) Local text-mode console
2) Local Graphical-mode Console
3) Remote Text-Mode console
4) Remote Graphical-Mode Console


Remote Login :-
 Linux remote access allows a user to access their Linux operating system from another computer. 
SSH :-
 Secure Socket Shell, is a protocol which allows you to connect securely to a remote computer or a server by using a interface.System and network administrators use this protocol the most
SSH client :-
 An SSH client is an application you install on the computer which you will use to connect to another computer or a server.
SSH Server :-
  SSH daemon that is constantly listening to a specific TCP/IP port for possible client connection requests.

Refer this to know the commands used for login :-
